SUMMARY:History Café: Seattle Mystic Al Hubbard
DESCRIPTION:Join Brad Holden\, author of Seattle Mystic Alfred M. Hubbard for a discussion of one of Seattle’s most mysterious figures. Hubbard first appeared in the papers in 1919 for his supposed invention of a perpetual motion machine that harnessed energy from Earth’s atmosphere. From there\, he transformed himself into a bootlegger\, radio pioneer\, top-secret spy\, and eventually “the Johnny Appleseed of LSD”. \nHistory Café is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink and MOHAI. \nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibility support\, email programs@mohai.org two weeks before the program. \nGrab some food for thought–light food and drink will be available to purchase in the atrium. \nIf you can’t make it to the museum\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this event.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-seattle-mystic-al-hubbard/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:History,Innovation,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/History-Cafe-Seattle-Mystic-Al-Hubbard_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
