SUMMARY:First Thursday - April
DESCRIPTION:Visit MOHAI on the First Thursday of every month for free admission to the museum’s permanent exhibits between 5—8 pm. \nFree admission includes access to all of MOHAI’s award winning exhibits\, including our temporary displays Riding Together: 135 Years of Cycling in Seattle\, TADAIMA: I’m Home and special exhibit Kickstands Up! 125 Years of Motorcycling in the PNW. Advance online tickets are not required\, but may be reserved below. \nFree admission also includes access to two special presentations of Living Voices in the Joshua Green Theater at 5:30 and 6:30pm. Seats are first-come first-served.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/first-thursday-april/
LOCATION:MOHAI\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:Entertainment
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/first_thursday_mar_hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
