SUMMARY:History Café: Preserving the Vision of Asahel Curtis
DESCRIPTION:Join Margaret Weatherbee\, Head of Collections at the Washington State Historical Society and History Museum\, for an in-depth look at the digitization and preservation of the Asahel Curtis Collection. This collection features over 42\,000 images by photographer Asahel Curtis (1873-1941) that document the evolution of life in the Pacific Northwest in the early 20th century. \nHistory Café is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink\, The Pacific Northwest Historians Guild\, and MOHAI. \nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibility support\, email programs@mohai.org before the program. \nGrab some food for thought–complimentary snacks and beverages will be provided. \nIf you can’t make it to the museum\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend this event.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-preserving-the-vision-of-asahel-curtis/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art,History,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Preserving-the-Vision-of-Asahel-Curtis_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
