SUMMARY:Meet the Cossacks: Seattle's Motorcycle Stunt and Drill Team
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the history of the Cossacks\, Seattle’s long strolling Motorcycle Stunt and Drill Team\, with Rob Root and other members. Since 1938\, the Seattle Cossacks have captured the imagination of audiences with great pyramids and other wonders of the motorcycling world. Following the presentation\, visitors are welcome to get up close and personal for photos with the team’s vintage Harleys! \nTickets for this program are free\, but do not include access to MOHAI’s exhibitions. If you would like to see all that MOHAI has to offer during your visit\, you can purchase museum admission here. \nFor more accessibility support\, email programs@mohai.org two weeks before the program.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/meet-the-cossacks-seattles-motorcycle-stunt-and-drill-team/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:History,Hobbies,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Meet-the-Cossacks_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
