SUMMARY:Behind the Seams: Roaring '20s
DESCRIPTION:Behind the Seams is back\, with a closer look at the artifacts than ever before! One hundred years later\, women’s fashions of the 1920s continue to shock and to dazzle. Hemlines rose up to the knee and eveningwear were built to move\, shake\, and sparkle. Join Curator of Collections\, Clara Berg for a historical overview and then an intimate viewing of the most stunning 1920s dresses from the museum collection. \nA member pre-sale for this event will begin on March 11 and run until March 23. Secure your spot early by becoming a MOHAI member today! \nFor accessibility support\, contact programs@mohai.org two weeks before the program.
URL:https://mohai.org/event/behind-the-seams-roaring-20s/
LOCATION:Norcliffe Conference Room\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, WA\, 98109\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art,Fashion,History,People & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mohai.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Behind-the-Seams-Roaring-20s_Hero.jpg
END:VEVENT
